    var bio = "Rev. Dr. Walter R. Gibson, Jr. was born and raised in Houston, TX. He is a graduate of Southern Methodist University (B.A.1994), and Houston Graduate School of Theology (M.A. and DMin 2001 & 2014). He served as Senior Pastor of Pilgrim Rest Baptist Church in Lansing, MI (2006-2014), where he was appointed President of The Church of Greater Lansing, a group of 40+  churches that served as the hands and feet of Jesus Christ to the least of these. Walter also served as Adjunct Professor of Spirituality (Grand Rapids Theological Seminary, 2019), featured lecturer for the Wolverine State Convention of Christian Education, Campus Crusade for Christ, and has hosted leadership conferences for the Holy Apostolic Reformed Church in Accra, Ghana. \n\n He has authored two books, No More Business as Usual (2006), and recently co-authored with his wife, You Two Can Have a Great Marriage (2021). \n\n Walter currently serves as a Resident Chaplain at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital. Walter  is married to the love of his life, Tarsha. They have two sons (Cameron and Christian); one daughter-in-love (Whitney), and a granddaughter, Wylie Cree."

